  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. Global Regulatory Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\n2. Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting\n- Cross-border financial transparency standards\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) protocols\n\n3. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Extradition agreements\n- International asset seizure procedures\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Information sharing between financial intelligence units\n\n4. Legal Harmonization\n- Standardizing definitions of money laundering\n- Creating consistent legal standards\n- Developing uniform investigation procedures\n- Establishing international prosecution protocols\n\n5. Technological Challenges\n- Addressing cryptocurrency transactions\n- Managing digital financial platforms\n- Tracking complex transnational financial networks\n- Developing adaptive regulatory technologies\n\nEach country implements these frameworks differently, but international cooperation aims to create comprehensive, interconnected legal approaches to preventing money laundering.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific aspects?",
